# Line-ending policy for DLLPickle.
#
# Goal: every text file is stored in the repository with LF blobs so diffs stay
# clean and consistent across platforms, while Windows-authored source and docs
# check out with CRLF working-tree endings. Normalizing here prevents the
# spurious CRLF/LF (and mixed-ending) churn that otherwise leaks into diffs.

# Baseline: let Git detect text vs. binary and normalize all text blobs to LF.
* text=auto

# Windows-authored content: force CRLF in the working tree on every platform so
# editors, PSScriptAnalyzer, and signing behave identically regardless of each
# contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
*.md     text eol=crlf
*.ps1    text eol=crlf
*.psm1   text eol=crlf
*.psd1   text eol=crlf
*.ps1xml text eol=crlf

# Binary assets: never apply line-ending conversion.
*.png binary
*.mp4 binary
*.zip binary
*.cab binary
